Wilbur Ross has been sworn in as the 39th Secretary of Commerce for the United States. Vice President Mike Pence administered the oath of office in a ceremony held in the Vice President's Ceremonial Office. Ross, a successful American businessman with over 40 years of experience, is expected to lead the Department of Commerce in fostering economic growth and creating jobs for Americans. President Trump and Vice President Pence expressed confidence in Ross' ability to succeed in this role. Ross expressed gratitude for the support and vowed to live up to the responsibilities of the position. He also expressed hope for bipartisan cooperation in building America's future. The ceremony concluded with Ross stating his readiness to get to work.